<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="tag">Tag</a> - A tag enables an experimenter to follow or extract a particular <a href="#molecule">molecule</a>, molecular species or even whole cells. <em>Exempli gratia</em> the His-tag enables experimenters to enrich for species containing said tag using columns (a nickel column for the His-tag). <a href="#fluorescence">Fluorescent</a> tags enable measurement with devices like plate readers or <a href="#facs">flow cytometers</a>.